nce, technology, engineering and mathematics: a strategy for Scotland (The Royal Society of Edinburgh), \nhttp://www.royalsoced.org.uk/cms/files/advice-papers/inquiry/women_in_stem/tapping_talents.pdf\n \n \nLondon Mathematical Society Good Practise Scheme - Advancing women's careers in university mathematical sciences departments, \nhttp://www.lms.ac.uk/sites/lms.ac.uk/files/files/GPS_Booklet_A5FINAL.pdf\n \nDaphne Jackson Trust \n–\n Annual Report 2011\n, \nhttp://www.daphnejackson.org/about/reports/DJT%20Annual%20Report%202011%20WEB.pdf\n \n Horizon 2020 – FAQ on promoting gender equality, \nhttp://ec.europa.eu/research/horizon2020/index_en.cfm?pg=faq&amp;sub=details&amp;idfaq=42055\n \nThe Nordic region - a step closer to gender balance in research?\n (Norden) \nhttp://www.norden.org/en/publications/publikationer/2013-544\n \n"